linesOfText.text: Lady Emma in her Land of Wonder,
every now and again fell under.
Under a bridge she should never have crossed,
Under a spell that just made her feel lost.

When trouble came knocking,
Emma knew what to do!
The same thing you’d do if it happened to you!

She climbed out of the water and shook herself dry!
She snapped out of the spell and told the witch,
“Bye!”

For most of her days she
felt fearless,
not small.

Then along came trouble and downward she'd fall.

Stumbling... and tumbling,

getting back on her feet,
she did fairly well
without skipping a beat!

Her father came running to help Emma out...
To straighten her up and to turn her about.

He was quick to her rescue through every dark day,
and made sure she was safe, once again on her way.

He helped her feel confident and tightly secure.
She was safe as could be and of that she was sure.
He protected her daily, kept her out of harm’s way.
He kept trolls in their place and dragons at bay.

When trouble came knocking,
Emma knew what to do!
The same thing you’d do if it happened to you!

She grew with such joy and,
yes, sometimes a blunder,
since a nearly-grown lady can still fall right under.

Her adventures were endless and full of delight.
Most times they’d go well, but sometimes not quite.
When her boat overturned in deep waters she fell,
Yet she did not panic and she did not yell.

When trouble came knocking,
Emma knew what to do!
The same thing you’d do
if it happened to you!

As Emma grew older, and time went along,
her prince stood beside her, so able and strong.
He helped her each day, like her dear father had
when good things would happen, or sometimes go bad.

One day Emma beamed,
ever so pleased,
“Wait father! Wait prince!”
she lovingly teased.

“You Sillies! I’ve got this!
I can’t wait and pout.
When I get into
mix-ups,
I’ll work myself out.”

Their support was the strongest,
best gift she received.
She knew they were near
and she truly believed
they would love and respect her for all of her days,
smile proudly and
enjoy her adventurous ways.

Ever after and happy in her own Land of Wonder,
now when Emma missteps and falls all asunder,
she jumps right back up and it doesn’t take long!
She’s earned her own way; it was there all along.
The End
But Really, Only The Beginning Of The Dream
